  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AparSymptoms
    Definition of the specific symptoms for each APAR rule
    DetermineOperationMode
    Determine the operational model of the AHU unit, according to APAR.
    DetermineSteadyStateOperationMode
    Determine the steady-state operational model of the AHU unit, according to APAR.
    RobustFDDparameters
    Definition of generic FDD parameters for the APAR rule set
    Rule1
    Implementation of Rule #1 of the APAR rule set: In heating mode, supply air temperature should be greater compared to mixed air temperature.
    Rule10
    Implementation of Rule #10 of the APAR rule set: Outside air temperature and mixed air temperature should be nearly the same.
    Rule11
    Implementation of Rule #11 of the APAR rule set: Supply air temperature should be lower compared to the mixed air temperature.
    Rule12
    Implementation of Rule #12 of the APAR rule set: Supply air temperature should be lower compared to the return air temperature.
    Rule13
    Implementation of Rule #13 of the APAR rule set: Cooling coil valve saturated fully open and persistent supply air temperature error exists.
    Rule14
    Implementation of Rule #14 of the APAR rule set: Cooling coil valve saturated fully open, if cooling load increases supply air temperature will drift from setpoint.
    Rule15
    Implementation of Rule #15 of the APAR rule set: Outside air temperature too low for mechanical cooling with minimum outside air.
    Rule16
    Implementation of Rule #16 of the APAR rule set: Supply air temperature should be lower compared to the mixed air temperature.
    Rule17
    Implementation of Rule #17 of the APAR rule set: Supply air temperature should be lower compared to the return air temperature.
    Rule18
    Implementation of Rule #18 of the APAR rule set: %outside air too low or too high.
    Rule19
    Implementation of Rule #19 of the APAR rule set: Cooling coil valve saturated fully open and persistent supply air temperature error exists.
    Rule2
    Implementation of Rule #1 of the APAR rule set: Outdoor air fraction too low or too high.
    Rule20
    Implementation of Rule #20 of the APAR rule set: Cooling coil valve saturated fully open, if cooling load increases supply air temperature will drift from setpoint.
    Rule21
    Implementation of Rule #21 of the APAR rule set: Heating coil valve, cooling coil valve and mixing box damper are modulating simultaneously.
    Rule22
    Implementation of Rule #22 of the APAR rule set: Heating coil and cooling coil valves are modulating simultaneously.
    Rule23
    Implementation of Rule #23 of the APAR rule set: Heating coil valve and and mixing box damper are modulating simultaneously.
    Rule24
    Implementation of Rule #24 of the APAR rule set: Cooling coil valve and mixing box damper are modulating simultaneously.
    Rule25
    Implementation of Rule #25 of the APAR rule set: Persistent supply air temperature error exists.
    Rule26
    Implementation of Rule #26 of the APAR rule set: Mixed air temperature should be between return air temperature and outside air temperature (mixed air temperature is too high).
    Rule27
    Implementation of Rule #27 of the APAR rule set: Mixed air temperature should be between return air temperature and outside air temperature (mixed air temperature is too low).
    Rule28
    Implementation of Rule #28 of the APAR rule set: Too many mode switches per hour.
    Rule3
    Implementation of Rule #3 of the APAR rule set: Heating coil valve saturated fully open and persistent supply air temperature error exists.
    Rule4
    Implementation of Rule #4 of the APAR rule set: Heating coil valve saturated fully open, if heating load increases supply air temperature will drift from setpoint.
    Rule5
    Implementation of Rule #5 of the APAR rule set: Outside air temperature too warm for cooling with outside air.
    Rule6
    Implementation of Rule #6 of the APAR rule set: Supply air temperature should be greater compared to the return air temperature.
    Rule7
    Implementation of Rule #7 of the APAR rule set: Supply air temperature and mixed air temperature should be nearly the same
    Rule8
    Implementation of Rule #8 of the APAR rule set: Outside air temperature too low for mechanical cooling with 100% outside air.
    Rule9
    Implementation of Rule #9 of the APAR rule set: Outside air temperature too high for mechanical cooling with 100% outside air.
